Search File in Directory
$ find ./ -name “*.pdf”
$ find /home/cadtc -name “*.jpg”

List file
$ ls -l
$ ls -la

Copy a File
$ cp ./a.test /home/cadtc/
$ cp ./a.test /home/cadtc/b.test

Move a File or Rename
$ mv ./a.test /home/cadtc/
$ mv ./a.test  ./b.test

Find a File that include the string
$ find ./linux/driver -name “*.c” | grep “LED”


SSH Copy  a File To Remote
$ scp ./a.test  root@192.168.0.100:/home/root


SSH Login To Remote
$ ssh  root@192.168.0.100


Install a kernel module
$ insmod hello_world.ko
$ modprobe hello_world.ko

Remove a kernel module
$ rmmod hello_world
$ modprobe -r hello_world

List kernel module live in kernel
$ lsmod

List mounted disk status
$ lsblk


Fdisk disk
$ sudo fdisk /dev/sdX


Format disk 
$ sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdx1


Mount disk 
$ mkdir /tmp/sdx_mount
$ mount /dev/sdX1 /tmp/sdx_mount

Password Modify 
$ passwd


Remove file or directory 
$ rm  /home/cadtc/test_file.txt

$ mkdir /home/cadtc/test_folder
$ rm  -r /home/cadtc/test_folder

Check Linux System Log 
$ dmesg
$ dmesg | tail

Extract tar.bz2 file
$ tar -xvjf  /home/cadtc/test.tar.bz2 -C /home/cadtc/test_folder


Extract tar.gz file
$ tar -xvzf  /home/cadtc/test.tar.gz -C /home/cadtc/test_folder
